## 1. `PkceServiceTest`

```java
package com.bnpp.pf.arthur.core.service;

import com.bnpp.pf.arthur.core.exception.TechnicalException;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;
import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;

class PkceServiceTest {

    private final PkceService pkceService = new PkceService();

    @Test
    void generateCodeChallenge_shouldReturnExpectedSha256Base64UrlValue() {
        String result = pkceService.generateCodeChallenge("verifier-123");

        assertThat(result).isNotBlank();
        assertThat(result).doesNotContain("=");
        assertThat(result).doesNotContain("+");
        assertThat(result).doesNotContain("/");
    }

    @Test
    void generateCodeChallenge_shouldReturnSameValueForSameVerifier() {
        String first = pkceService.generateCodeChallenge("verifier-123");
        String second = pkceService.generateCodeChallenge("verifier-123");

        assertThat(first).isEqualTo(second);
    }

    @Test
    void generateCodeChallenge_shouldThrowException_whenVerifierIsNull() {
        assertThatThrownBy(() -> pkceService.generateCodeChallenge(null))
                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)
                .hasMessage("codeVerifier must not be blank");
    }

    @Test
    void generateCodeChallenge_shouldThrowException_whenVerifierIsBlank() {
        assertThatThrownBy(() -> pkceService.generateCodeChallenge(" "))
                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)
                .hasMessage("codeVerifier must not be blank");
    }
}
```

No need to test `NoSuchAlgorithmException` branch. `SHA-256` is guaranteed by the JDK, so that branch is practically unreachable. Sonar may still mark it partially uncovered; acceptable.

